##Manual Configuration via Portal  ##
Step 1: Create Logic App
Navigate to Azure Portal → Create a resource

Search "Logic App"

Click Create

Configure:

Subscription: Your subscription

Resource Group: SOC-lab-01

Logic App name: AWS-Sentinel-Email-Better

Region: East US

Plan type: Consumption

Click Review + Create → Create

Step 2: Add Sentinel Incident Trigger
Open the Logic App → Logic app designer

Search "Sentinel"

Select When a Microsoft Sentinel incident is created

Configure:

Workspace: soclawlab

Severity Filter: High, Critical

Status Filter: New

Step 3: Add Condition - Check Incident Status
Click + New step

Search "Condition"

Configure:

text
@triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['status']
is not equal to
Closed
Step 4: Add Severity Check (Inside TRUE branch)
Inside TRUE branch, add another Condition

Configure:

text
@triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['severity']
is equal to
High
OR
@triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['severity']
is equal to
Critical
Step 5: Add Update Incident Status (Inside severity TRUE branch)
Click Add an action

Search "Sentinel"

Select Update incident

Configure:

Workspace: soclawlab

Incident ID: @{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['incidentNumber']}

Status: In Progress

Owner: security-automation@soclab.com

Step 6: Add Add Incident Tags
Click Add an action

Search "Sentinel"

Select Add incident tags

Configure:

Workspace: soclawlab

Incident ID: @{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['incidentNumber']}

Tags:

auto-remediation

cross-cloud

critical-incident

Step 7: Add Send Email Action
Click Add an action

Search "Outlook"

Select Send an email (V2)

Configure:

To: ir-responder@gmail.com; olamilake95@gmail.com

Subject: 🚨 CRITICAL INCIDENT - @{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['title']}

Body: (HTML template from workflow.json)

Step 8: Add HTTP Action to Call AWS API Gateway
Click Add an action

Search "HTTP"

Select HTTP

Configure:

Method: POST

URI: Your API Gateway URL (e.g., https://xxxxxxxxxx.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod/remediate)

Headers:

Content-Type: application/json

Body:

json
{
  "incident_id": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['incidentNumber']}",
  "incident_type": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['title']}",
  "severity": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['severity']}",
  "threat_type": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['additionalData']?['customDetails']?['ThreatCategory'][0]}",
  "source_ip": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['additionalData']?['customDetails']?['SourceIP'][0]}",
  "username": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['additionalData']?['customDetails']?['UserType'][0]}",
  "aws_region": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['additionalData']?['customDetails']?['AWSRegion'][0]}",
  "actions_detected": "@{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['additionalData']?['customDetails']?['ActionsDetected'][0]}"
}
Step 9: Add Condition to Process Lambda Response
Click Add an action after HTTP

Add Condition

Configure:

text
@outputs('HTTP')?['statusCode']
is equal to
200
Step 10: Add Success Comment (TRUE branch)
Inside TRUE branch, add Add incident comment action

Configure:

Workspace: soclawlab

Incident ID: @{triggerBody()?['object']?['properties']?['incidentNumber']}

Message:

text
✅ Auto-Remediation Successful

Lambda Response: @{outputs('HTTP')?['body']}

Actions Performed:
- IAM access keys disabled
- Email alert sent
- Idempotency record created

Response Time: <30 seconds
Step 11: Add Failure Comment (FALSE branch)
Inside FALSE branch, add Add incident comment action

Configure:

Message:

text
❌ Auto-Remediation Failed

Error: HTTP @{outputs('HTTP')?['statusCode']}
Response: @{outputs('HTTP')?['body']}

Manual intervention required.
Step 12: Save and Test
Click Save in the top menu

Run Trigger → Run

Verify the workflow in Runs history